translationBlock.key: Add to inventory the specified item. The specifier must be a location array, entity UUID, or virtual inventory id. The items are distributed in the inventory, first filling up slots that have the same item type, up to the max stack size, then fills up empty slots, until either the entire inventory is filled, or the entire amount has been given. If the inventory is full, number of items that were not added is returned, which will be less than or equal to the quantity provided. Otherwise, returns 0.
